The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Monday, December 02, 2002  Calcutta Column
				 																																									Flocks of sheep, goats, cows and buffaloes are often seen on main roads, blocking the traffic and inconveniencing people. An hour should be set aside every afternoon, when these animals can be allowed onto the streets. They not only cause traffic problems, but are also a safety hazard. Moreover, they dirty the roads. 				 																																									B. N. Bose,				 																																									Dum Dum.				 																																									During winter, a large number of people visit the zoo. It used to open at 6 am, but now does so at 9 am. This deprives visitors of the memorable experience of early morning bird and animal activity. In addition, the entrance queue often extends up to National Library, later in the day.				 																																									Piyal Mukherjee,				 																																									Lake Town.
